ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is the require physical chemistry seminar series. Nothing special.
Yes, because it is a great opportunity to learn other people's research.
I would recommend to my fellow students. It's resourceful.
The seminar series gives a good overview of modern chemistry and the leaders in the various sub-disciplines.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It's good to see what other people are working on and to get some ideas while having lunch with them and other students. The career advice the non-professors can give is priceless.
This course allows you to gain insight from various researches.
It's a good opportunity to hear about and have discussion on cutting edge topics.
Some of the talks were insightful and also fostered new collaborations.
